name: Event survey questions for attendees
description: Design a survey to gather feedback from your event attendees.

nodes.name: llm
nodes.title: Answers
nodes.description: Answer a question using a large language model. Chat history can be used to maintain context between messages.

input_config.human_message:
Develop an event survey with 8-10 questions to assess {{event_name}} {{survey_questions}} {{optional}} and its impact on the attendees.
Example:
Sure! Here is a sample event survey with 8 questions to assess [event name] and its impact on the attendees:
How likely are you to recommend [event name] to a friend or colleague?
Very likely
Likely
Neutral
Unlikely
Very unlikely
How would you rate the overall organization and logistics of [event name]?
Excellent
Good
Average
Poor
Very poor
Did [event name] meet your expectations?
Yes, it exceeded my expectations
Yes, it met my expectations
No, it did not meet my expectations
What was the highlight of [event name] for you?
Free text response
Did you find the content presented during the event relevant and valuable?
Very relevant and valuable
Relevant and valuable
Neutral
Not very relevant and valuable
Not relevant and valuable at all
How would you rate the quality of the speakers at [event name]?
Excellent
Good
Average
Poor
Very poor
What did you like most about [event name]?
Free text response
How likely are you to attend [event name] next year?
Very likely
Likely
Neutral
Unlikely
Very unlikely

optional.title: Optional
optional.description: You can also specify the order you want the questions to appear and any answer choices for multiple-choice questions.

ui_metadata.value: Open Ended: What is one key takeaway you will implement in your own social media marketing strategy?

survey_questions.title: Survey Questions
survey_questions.description: A list of questions you want to ask attendees about their experience (multiple choice, open ended, or rating scale)
